quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  2,238,"Preserve<sup>pl </sup>the prayers and the middle prayer, and stand devout before Allah."
  2,239,"But if you<sup>pl </sup>are in fear, then<i>(pray) </i>on foot or while riding. Then when you feel secure, remember Allah as He has taught you what you did not know."
  2,240,"Moreover, those of you<i>(men) </i>who are taken at death and leave spouses behind—(let them bequeath)a bequest{1}for their spouses with compensation for a year without eviction<i>(from the husband’s residence) </i>. But if they depart, then no sin is committed by you<sup>pl </sup>regarding what they have done with themselves in accordance with what is fair. For Allah is Almighty, All-Wise.",1:[Qira’at: All except Abu Amr, Ibn Amer, Hafs and Hamza read it as: “…and leave spouses behind—a bequest (is ordained upon them) for their spouses with compensation…”]
  2,241,"And for divorced women there is a compensation in accordance with what is fair—a duty upon the mindful<sup>pl </sup>."
  2,242,"Allah thus makes His signs evident to you<sup>pl </sup>, that you may reason."
  2,243,"Have you<sup>sg </sup>not seen those who departed their homes by the thousands, for fear of death? So Allah said to them, “Die,” then He revived them. Most surely, Allah is Gracious towards mankind, but most of mankind do not thank."
  2,244,"And combat<sup>pl </sup>in the way of Allah, and know that Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing."
  2,245,"Who is it that will lend Allah a good loan?(So)that He may multiply it for him manifold{1}, forAllah withholds and extends, and to Him you<sup>pl </sup>are returned{2}.",1:[Qira’at: All except for Asem, Ibn Amer and Ya’qub read it as: “Who is it that will lend Allah a good loan (so) that He may multiply it for him manifold? For Allah withholds and extends,”],2:[Qira’at: Ya’qub read it as: “…you<sup><small>pl</small></sup> return.”]
